{
    "name":  "Irish Stew",
    "instructions":  "1. Heat the oil in a large stockpot over medium heat. Add the lamb pieces and cook, stirring gently, until evenly browned. Season with salt and pepper.  \n\n2. Stir in the onion and cook for a few minutes. Stir in the water and add the carrots. Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer until lamb is tender, about 45 minutes.  \n\n3. Stir in the potatoes and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, before adding the leeks and rosemary. Continue to simmer uncovered, until potatoes are tender but still whole.  \n\n4. Serve piping hot in bowls garnished with fresh parsley.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Brown lamb in oil and season.  \n\n2. Add onion, then water and carrots, simmer for 45 mins.  \n\n3. Add potatoes, cook 20 mins, then add leeks and rosemary, simmer until potatoes are tender.  \n\n4. Serve hot, garnish with parsley.",
